main event: An unidentified object was detected on radar over Palmdale, California on September 19, 1953, exhibiting high speed and unusual maneuverability.
interesting points: The object was initially detected at an altitude of 3,500 feet and estimated to be 19 x 45 miles in size.
The object appeared white with bright puffs of smoke or vapor emitting from it.
The object climbed to an altitude of 50,000 feet in just 2 minutes, gaining 35,000 feet.
The object then descended while gaining speed up to 1,900 mph, before executing a 35-mile dash at the same high speed.
Attempts to intercept the object with C-47 and F-94C aircraft were unsuccessful, as the object maneuvered in an uncontrollable manner.
sighted object: a large, white, high-speed unidentified object
